The defendant Shane M. Sueoka was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Delivery of Schedule I, II or III Non-Narcotics, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(1)(b).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Statement by Attorney Blader regarding resolution. 14CF171-Preliminary hearing address-defendant waives preliminary hearing. Court has read the complaint, finds probable cause and enters an order binding the defendant over for trial. Information filed. Attorney Templeton confirms receipt and waives formal reading.   Defendant advised of minimum/maximum penalty.  Plea QN reviewed w/Defendant.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained. Chapter 950 compliance addressed.  Plea:  No Contest. Court accepts plea and enters JOC. Court dismisses outright Count 2. Sentencing argument by DA Blader. Sentencing argument by Attorney Templeton. Statement by the defendant. Court sentences the defendant to: SWD and places the defendant on probation for a period of 3 years. CONDITIONS: 75 days WCJ-No Good Time Credit.   The defendant must maintain absolute sobriety and is prohibited from possessing any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician. AODA and follow through. No Contact with Amanda Hopp and/or Shawn Knaup. Costs to be paid within 60 days or payment plan. Buy money of $80.00. Appeal Rights Given. 
12CM110 & 12CM457: 149 days WCJ on each case, credit for 112 days served. Time Served.  Court re-imposes costs. Court reinstitutes payment plan, lifts stay on contempt and is to commence on April 1, 2015.
